🚖 Cab Booking System – Documentation
1. 📌 Introduction

The Cab Booking System is a web-based application that allows users to book cabs online, track ride details, and manage bookings efficiently. The system provides separate functionalities for users, drivers, and administrators.

2. 🎯 Objectives
To provide an easy and fast cab booking experience
To manage users, drivers, and bookings efficiently
To reduce manual errors in booking management
To ensure secure and reliable ride allocation
3. 🧩 System Modules
👤 User Module
User Registration & Login
Book a Cab
View Booking History
Cancel Booking
🚗 Driver Module
Driver Registration
Accept/Reject Ride Requests
View Assigned Rides
🛠️ Admin Module
Manage Users
Manage Drivers
View All Bookings
Assign Drivers
4. 🏗️ System Architecture

The system follows a 3-tier architecture:

Frontend: User interface (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)
Backend: Business logic (PHP / Node.js)
Database: Data storage (MySQL)
5. 🗄️ Database Design
📊 Tables Used
1. Users Table
user_id (Primary Key)
name
email
password
phone
2. Drivers Table
driver_id (Primary Key)
name
vehicle_details
phone
availability_status
3. Bookings Table
booking_id (Primary Key)
user_id (Foreign Key)
driver_id (Foreign Key)
pickup_location
drop_location
booking_status
date_time
6. 🔄 Workflow
User logs into the system
User enters pickup & drop location
System checks available drivers
Driver is assigned to the booking
Ride status is updated
User can view or cancel booking
7. 💻 Technologies Used
Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Backend: PHP / Node.js
Database: MySQL
Version Control: Git & GitHub
8. 🔐 Security Features
User authentication (Login system)
Password protection
